{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Reaper Scripts for Game Audio and Sound Design\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is a database of scripts that I wrote for Reaper DAW. Sharing them here for the game audio community as well. Enjoy!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 SWS, js_ReaScriptAPI and ReaImGui extensions are required to be installed for scripts to work correctly.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can install these scripts by using ReaPack. In Reaper, go to the menu bar: Extension > ReaPack > Import Repositories... and copy and past the link below into the dialogue box.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mcheung-dev/reaperScripts/refs/heads/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Tools\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 MC_Variation Generator - One-Click Variations!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This tool is designed to make variations creation easy. One tap to duplicates your layers, randomizes key parameters, and region creation for effortless variety.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e15c8622-5a9f-43a9-b3a0-6a183810f0dc]\cf0}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Implode Takes Feature\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/796e628f-b96e-41bc-b888-24b4b2a340eb]\cf0}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 MC_FastFileRenamer - Batch File Renamer Tool\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This tool is designed to assist with renaming media items within Reaper. It replicates the functionality of the FastFileRenamer desktop app, enabling you to replace, remove, and insert naming patterns effortlessly\u8212-all with a single click.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7983ed5b-69e5-49f4-bd9c-79d50b4f5cd9]\cf0}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Scripts List\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Auto Increment Duplicate Regions}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Automatically renames duplicate regions with incremental numbers (_01, _02, etc.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Particularly useful for organizing render export regions\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Auto Increment Items}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Automatically renames selected items with incremental numbers, works with different naming patterns (eg SFX_01, SFX_02, SFX_03, VO_01, VO_02, VO_03)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Create Region from Selected Items}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Creates a new region that encompasses all currently selected items\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Mousewheel Item Rate}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Adjusts media item playback rate using the mousewheel\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Move items to mouse location}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Moves selected items to the current mouse cursor position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Quick repositioning of media without dragging\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Move Muted Tracks to Bottom Except VIDEO & REFERENCE}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Organizes project by moving muted tracks to the bottom\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Preserves the position of tracks named "VIDEO" or "REFERENCE"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Move Muted Tracks to Bottom of Folder Except VIDEO & REFERENCE}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Moves muted tracks to the bottom within their folder structure\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Preserves the position of tracks named "VIDEO" or "REFERENCE"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Move Selected Tracks to Top Below VIDEO & REFERENCE}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Repositions selected tracks to the top of the project just below tracks named "VIDEO" or "REFERENCE"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Remove Unused Tracks}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Identifies and removes tracks that don't contain any media items (feel free to adjust the .lua for specific properties)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Helps clean up visual clutter\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Render Time Selection to Stereo}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Renders the current time selection to a stereo file to track below, mute original\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_RepositionItems}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Arranges selected items sequentially with specified gaps (default 0.5, adjust .lua for time value)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Useful for organizing sound effects or dialogue clips\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Reset MediaItem Rate}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Resets playback rate of selected items to original speed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Adjusts item length & perserves fade properties\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Select items under length threshold on selected tracks}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Selects items that are shorter than a specified duration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Helps identify and manage very short audio clips for batch processing/deletion\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\i mc_Set All Tracks to 0dB}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Resets the fader of all tracks to (unity gain)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Quick way to normalize track volumes\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Troubleshooting\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Q: I'm getting this error: ImGui__init: ReaImGui 0.9.1 is too old (action requires API 0.9.3.2 or newer)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A: Your ReaImGui is out of date. To update, go to Extensions --> ReaPack --> Browse Packages --> Right click on ReaImGui & Update\sa180\par}
